Headlines.Headline: Apax Poised To Sell Travelex To Western Union For $1B - Source

PARAGRAPH.#text: By Marietta Cauchi Of DOW JONES NEWSWIRES LONDON (Dow Jones)--Apax Partners is close to selling the business payments arm of Travelex to Western Union for $1 billion, a person familiar with the situation told Dow Jones Newswires Monday. Headlines.Author: Dow Jones
Headlines.Headline: Don't Bail So Fast On Hot Stocks, Fund Manager Says

PARAGRAPH.#text: By Dow Jones BOSTON (Dow Jones) -- Andrew Meister, a portfolio manager for the Thrivent Small Cap Stock fund, says that investors should avoid "cutting your flowers to water your weeds," meaning that they might want to hold on to stocks that have been hot and ride them through a pullback, rather than taking their profits and sprinkling the money on new issues that might never bloom. In a radio interview with Chuck Jaffe, MarketWatch senior columnist, Meister said that some investors are bailing out on hot industries like shipping, fearing a reversal of fortune, at a time when he thinks the business is due for a short setback before becoming a buy again.
